line_1: If he the laughing muscles moves,
line_2: If he repeats, if he approves,

line_1: As thro' the woods with cautious step he moves.

line_1: And at thy Name alone she sighs, and moves.

line_1: And see! distinguish'd from the crowd he moves,
line_2: Each finger marks him, and each eye approves!

line_1: Psyche, with strength revived, now onward moves
line_2: Freed from the mazes of Disfida's groves,

line_1: Nor know we as life onward moves,
line_2: NOT every gem a diamond proves,

line_1: How distant your machine from either moves.
line_2: On Reason and Newtonian rules he proves,

line_1: Led by a tenderness his Courage moves,
line_2: Like Mars's Chariot, drawn by Venus Doves.

line_1: Not half so swiftly the fierce Eagle moves,
line_2: When thro' the Clouds he drives the trembling Doves;

line_1: Each rising art by just gradation moves,
line_2: Toil builds on toil, and age on age improves:

line_1: The obedient Steel with living instinct moves,
line_2: And veers for ever to the pole it loves.

line_1: Bends o'er the car, and whirling, as it moves,
line_2: His loosen'd bowstring, drives the rising doves.

line_1: Erewhile aloft in wanton circles moves,
line_2: And woos on Hymen-wings his velvet loves.

line_1: But far away alas! that Prospect moves,
line_2: Lost in the Clouds, like distant Hills and Groves,

line_1: No Nymph so nimbly swims, so graceful moves.
line_2: Happy the Youth, whom beauteous Myra loves,

line_1: With fine librations quivering as it moves.
line_2: So turns the needle to the pole it loves,

line_1: As round the wild meandering coast she moves
line_2: By gushing rills, rude cliffs, and nodding groves;

line_1: As o'er the steeps with pausing foot she moves,
line_2: The pitying Dryads shriek amid their groves;

line_1: With soft suspended step Attention moves,
line_2: And Silence hovers o'er the listening groves;

line_1: As with nice touch her plaistic hand she moves,
line_2: Rise the fine forms of Beauties, Graces, Loves;

line_1: Soft breathes the gale, the current gently moves,

line_2: And wins the damsel to illicit loves.

line_1: Yet the pure stream moves on, and, as it moves,

line_1: Love then within a larger Circle moves,

line_1: With eager beats his Mechlin cravat moves;
